AB  - We establish a hybrid simulation model based on an approach combining agent-based model (ABM), discrete event simulation (DES), and system dynamics (SD) model, then provide a general modeling process. In ABM, infected patients will choose whether to enter DES based on the availability of medical resources, and both ABM and DES will transmit information about the recorded number of infections and hospital admissions to SD, thus forming interactions between the three models. Considering various influencing factors, hybrid simulation model establishes 45 scenarios to conduct joint evaluations of interventions. The results indicate that a combination of joint intervention strategies (strict government intervention and a 40% increase in medical resources) optimally identify epidemic inflection points, resource allocation, and actual medical costs. The hybrid simulation model provides effective solutions and recommendations for intervention in different infectious diseases, thereby facilitating the design of more rational decision-making strategies and fiscal budget allocations.
